  "body": "### Component\n\nCast\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n`forge 0.2.0 (fb4a836 2022-10-18T00:12:04.315108Z)`\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\ncast create2\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI am not discounting the possibility that I'm making a mistake but I'm not able to reproduce the salt/address combinations reported by `cast create2`.\r\n\r\nHere is a script you can run to demonstrate the difference:\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!/bin/sh\r\n\r\nset -e\r\n\r\nINIT_CODE_HASH=0x8117a76146b52c01f79ae3b7f0e04ef9ac84a00974c0144222ded76ab3dadcf3\r\nDEPLOYER=0x4e59b44847b379578588920ca78fbf26c0b4956c\r\n\r\nfunction computeAddress() {\r\n    local INIT=$1\r\n    salt=$(cast create2 \\\r\n        --init-code $INIT \\\r\n        --ends-with dead \\\r\n        --deployer $DEPLOYER \\\r\n        | tee create2.log | grep Salt | cut -d' ' -f2)\r\n\r\n    hex_salt=$(cast --to-base $salt 16)\r\n    hex_data=$(cast --concat-hex 0xff $DEPLOYER $hex_salt $INIT_CODE_HASH)\r\n    hashed_data=$(cast keccak $hex_data)\r\n\r\n    echo 'using salt' $hex_salt\r\n    echo 'expected addr:' $(grep 'Address' create2.log | cut -d' ' -f2)\r\n    echo 'computed addr:' $(echo $hashed_data | python3 -c 'import sys; print(f\"0x{sys.stdin.read()[-41:]}\")')\r\n}\r\n\r\necho 'using cast create2 --init-code $INIT_CODE_HASH'\r\ncomputeAddress $INIT_CODE_HASH\r\n```\r\n\r\nI get the following output:\r\n\r\n```\r\nusing cast create2 --init-code $INIT_CODE_HASH\r\nusing salt 0x202d80facd2c9fc71b201f7548f4cb371f413d841941924a2a05375de64861d3\r\nexpected addr: 0xce64Cef6d988fd714714835949edc483055Bdead\r\ncomputed addr: 0xa766d80f7a8f85954cdbe27a86af88d2bb515dc6\r\n```\r\n\r\n(the expected addr ends with `dead` but not the computed addr)\r\n\r\nThe computed address matches what I get when I deploy with `new Contract{salt}()` using `forge script`",
